WEBVTT

00:00:08.320 --> 00:00:10.560
The two young masters

00:00:10.640 --> 00:00:13.920
were so adorable.

00:00:14.000 --> 00:00:18.920
The older one was a boy,
handsome since he was little.

00:00:20.320 --> 00:00:22.320
As for the younger one…

00:00:25.120 --> 00:00:26.640
Oh, dear.

00:00:27.240 --> 00:00:31.520
They were still small when that happened.

00:00:36.080 --> 00:00:38.040
What happened, Grandma?

00:00:38.920 --> 00:00:42.400
They passed away
when they were still little.

00:00:43.200 --> 00:00:44.920
Grandma, do you remember their names?

00:00:45.000 --> 00:00:46.200
What were they called?

00:00:47.200 --> 00:00:49.400
The older one was named…

00:00:52.840 --> 00:00:54.280
Named…

00:00:54.360 --> 00:00:56.880
Um, what about the younger one?

00:01:04.200 --> 00:01:05.239
Nok,

00:01:06.080 --> 00:01:08.320
when did your daughter
get herself a husband?

00:01:08.400 --> 00:01:10.360
Hey, Grandma, no.

00:01:10.960 --> 00:01:13.960
These two came from Bangkok.

00:01:14.040 --> 00:01:16.120
She's not my daughter Daeng, Grandma.

00:01:16.200 --> 00:01:17.720
Um, sorry about that.

00:01:19.040 --> 00:01:21.480
You've got it mixed up.

00:01:21.560 --> 00:01:23.640
How is she not?

00:01:24.760 --> 00:01:27.360
This is your daughter.

00:01:28.600 --> 00:01:30.480
No, Grandma.

00:01:31.600 --> 00:01:33.480
It's okay.

00:01:33.560 --> 00:01:36.760
Grandma, please take care of your health.

00:01:36.840 --> 00:01:39.160
We'll come visit again.

00:01:39.840 --> 00:01:40.680
Alright.

00:01:41.720 --> 00:01:42.680
They'll come visit again.

00:01:42.760 --> 00:01:43.800
Did you hear that?

00:04:15.080 --> 00:04:18.480
Grandma Aom insisted firmly that Ms. Ampha

00:04:18.560 --> 00:04:21.920
had two children, one here,

00:04:22.000 --> 00:04:23.640
and one here.

00:04:23.720 --> 00:04:25.880
And her husband…

00:04:30.400 --> 00:04:33.080
ran off with his mistress.

00:04:36.040 --> 00:04:38.680
I'm sorry, Ms. Ampha.

00:04:38.760 --> 00:04:40.360
That's what Grandma Aom said.

00:04:41.080 --> 00:04:44.360
And Ms. Ampha said
she was locked up, right, Kluay?

00:04:45.200 --> 00:04:46.280
Yes.

00:04:47.400 --> 00:04:49.720
That's the feeling she conveyed to me.

00:04:49.800 --> 00:04:53.320
But she didn't say who did it
or where she's being held.

00:04:53.840 --> 00:04:57.480
Is that why Ms. Ampha keeps following you?

00:04:57.560 --> 00:05:01.960
Even though Mr. Warat
can't communicate with her?

00:05:02.040 --> 00:05:04.600
She's waiting to meet you, obviously.

00:05:04.680 --> 00:05:06.000
Can't you figure that out?

00:05:08.120 --> 00:05:12.120
Let me piece together everything we know.

00:05:12.200 --> 00:05:16.280
Ms. Ampha
had a relationship with Mr. Wichan,

00:05:16.360 --> 00:05:18.240
Mr. Warat's father.

00:05:18.320 --> 00:05:22.200
Mrs. Wanee didn't accept Ms. Ampha
as her daughter-in-law.

00:05:22.880 --> 00:05:24.800
Ms. Ampha had two children.

00:05:24.880 --> 00:05:28.200
They were probably Mr. Wichan's.

00:05:28.280 --> 00:05:32.000
When I saw the vision,
she used the word "My child."

00:05:32.600 --> 00:05:37.560
And when she tried to communicate
that she was locked up,

00:05:37.640 --> 00:05:39.520
she referred to herself as "Mom."

00:05:40.600 --> 00:05:42.240
And what about Ms. Praewilai,

00:05:43.160 --> 00:05:46.400
your mother on your birth certificate?

00:05:47.600 --> 00:05:52.600
Your grandmother firmly insists
that Ms. Ampha

00:05:52.680 --> 00:05:53.960
is not your mother.

00:05:56.640 --> 00:05:57.720
It's funny.

00:05:59.000 --> 00:06:01.440
Last time,
when we were investigating Jirasin,

00:06:02.760 --> 00:06:04.760
I wondered whether my father

00:06:05.680 --> 00:06:07.200
was really my father.

00:06:08.840 --> 00:06:09.920
And now

00:06:11.360 --> 00:06:12.760
I'm wondering whether my mother

00:06:13.880 --> 00:06:15.240
is really my mother.

00:06:19.720 --> 00:06:23.960
I think we should shift back to
the matter of Ms. Ampha being locked up.

00:06:24.040 --> 00:06:24.880
I agree.

00:06:24.960 --> 00:06:26.880
If we can untangle that,

00:06:27.480 --> 00:06:29.040
the rest will be much easier.

00:06:29.120 --> 00:06:30.680
Based on what we know so far,

00:06:31.720 --> 00:06:34.320
who might have had reason
to harm Ms. Ampha?

00:06:34.400 --> 00:06:36.560
At the top of my mind,

00:06:36.640 --> 00:06:40.080
it's Mrs. Wanee. A typical mother-in-law
versus daughter-in-law situation.

00:06:40.160 --> 00:06:42.880
Mm. And you? Who do you think?

00:06:50.080 --> 00:06:53.400
Grandma may be strict,
but she's not that cruel.

00:06:55.160 --> 00:06:57.360
If anyone did it,

00:06:57.960 --> 00:07:00.280
it would be someone
who lost something from this situation.

00:07:01.520 --> 00:07:02.800
Who was it?

00:07:04.800 --> 00:07:05.920
My mom?

00:07:08.840 --> 00:07:10.720
This wedding photo

00:07:10.800 --> 00:07:12.360
of Ms. Ampha

00:07:12.960 --> 00:07:15.000
was taken after

00:07:15.600 --> 00:07:17.160
Ms. Praewilai passed away.

00:07:18.320 --> 00:07:22.120
I got these images and enlarged them,

00:07:22.840 --> 00:07:24.400
there are dates written on them.

00:07:25.120 --> 00:07:28.080
Ms. Ampha might have
raised me since I was little.

00:07:29.320 --> 00:07:30.600
I agree.

00:07:31.280 --> 00:07:32.760
When you saw the vision,

00:07:33.640 --> 00:07:34.880
how old were the children?

00:07:36.440 --> 00:07:40.160
Probably about two or three years old.

00:07:40.240 --> 00:07:42.440
The timing matches perfectly.

00:07:43.120 --> 00:07:44.880
My mother passed away around then.

00:07:45.720 --> 00:07:47.360
Perfect match, Mr. Arnon.

00:07:47.440 --> 00:07:51.120
Is it possible
that after Ms. Praewilai died,

00:07:51.200 --> 00:07:52.040
Ms. Ampha

00:07:52.640 --> 00:07:54.920
took you in as an adopted son?

00:08:18.320 --> 00:08:23.960
WAKE UP, WORK, EXERCISE. HEALTH IS WEALTH.

00:08:29.040 --> 00:08:32.039
TRANSFER COMPLETE

00:08:40.559 --> 00:08:43.760
Na, you don't have to
come here to watch me.

00:08:44.280 --> 00:08:47.400
You can go back to your room
or go to the office first.

00:08:49.040 --> 00:08:50.240
I'm not here to watch you.

00:08:50.840 --> 00:08:54.080
But you've just been on your phone
the whole time.

00:08:54.160 --> 00:08:56.160
I said I'm not here to watch you.

00:08:56.240 --> 00:08:57.240
Then what's wrong?

00:09:01.200 --> 00:09:02.840
The evidence is clear.

00:09:02.920 --> 00:09:05.760
The transfer slip
proving you hired people to attack Kluay.

00:09:05.840 --> 00:09:08.880
I'm posting it on my socials today.

00:09:08.960 --> 00:09:10.040
I'll blur the name.

00:09:10.680 --> 00:09:13.360
If by tomorrow,
you don't come clear things up,

00:09:13.440 --> 00:09:18.400
I'll reveal your name and go live
when I drag them to the police station.

00:09:20.320 --> 00:09:21.400
I'll kill her.

00:09:21.480 --> 00:09:24.440
Na, stop acting crazy.

00:09:24.520 --> 00:09:25.520
You did this to yourself.

00:09:25.600 --> 00:09:27.440
Kluay is pretending.

00:09:28.200 --> 00:09:30.080
Acting like she won't press charges.

00:09:30.960 --> 00:09:32.080
See?

00:09:32.680 --> 00:09:36.560
She's not as meek
and innocent as you think.

00:09:39.080 --> 00:09:40.960
I'll take you to apologize to Kluay.

00:09:41.680 --> 00:09:43.280
Just admit your mistake.

00:09:43.360 --> 00:09:44.680
She'll forgive you.

00:09:44.760 --> 00:09:45.600
-If you…
-Enough.

00:09:47.000 --> 00:09:48.160
Stop talking.

00:10:03.720 --> 00:10:06.480
You must be throwing a tantrum now,

00:10:06.560 --> 00:10:10.120
you amoeba, protozoa,
soggy trash, rotten mess,

00:10:10.200 --> 00:10:12.560
psycho, you…

00:10:15.360 --> 00:10:17.400
Don't you have work to do?

00:10:18.200 --> 00:10:21.400
You just spend time insulting people.

00:10:21.480 --> 00:10:24.720
I'm on a break. No slacking here.

00:10:25.640 --> 00:10:27.440
I have to thank you so, so much, Arnon.

00:10:27.520 --> 00:10:31.880
Your investigation team works so fast.

00:10:32.400 --> 00:10:34.920
That transfer slip was the best.

00:10:35.000 --> 00:10:37.400
I was about to scold you.

00:10:37.480 --> 00:10:40.840
If you posted it immediately
after I sent it to you,

00:10:40.920 --> 00:10:44.320
she could sue for defamation,
even with the name blurred.

00:10:44.400 --> 00:10:45.960
Good. Let her sue.

00:10:46.040 --> 00:10:49.120
Then I'll have the right to dig into
where that money came from.

00:10:49.200 --> 00:10:52.200
Let's see who gets more hurt.

00:10:52.280 --> 00:10:54.640
And what exactly
are you after from Ameena?

00:10:54.720 --> 00:10:56.280
You'll see.

00:10:57.160 --> 00:11:01.360
They've bullied my sister for too long.

00:11:01.440 --> 00:11:03.760
This vicious cycle has to end.

00:11:04.920 --> 00:11:07.120
So, did you need something?

00:11:07.800 --> 00:11:09.200
Ms. Kluay's bracelet.

00:11:09.880 --> 00:11:12.560
Right now,
she's in a meeting with Mr. Warat.

00:11:18.280 --> 00:11:20.080
This is the first time

00:11:20.160 --> 00:11:22.040
I've kept a secret from Kluay.

00:11:22.560 --> 00:11:24.400
If she finds out, she'll be so hurt.

00:11:25.120 --> 00:11:27.120
What are you
going to do about the bracelet?

00:11:27.200 --> 00:11:28.840
Trace the manufacturer.

00:11:28.920 --> 00:11:30.680
There's a gold code on it.

00:11:34.400 --> 00:11:39.040
And if we find out
who Kluay's parents or relatives are,

00:11:39.120 --> 00:11:41.640
are we really going to tell her?

00:11:41.720 --> 00:11:43.480
I don't even want that day to come.

00:11:43.560 --> 00:11:45.120
I understand.

00:11:47.440 --> 00:11:50.240
Mama Toi must have her reasons

00:11:50.880 --> 00:11:53.400
for asking us to investigate.

00:11:56.480 --> 00:11:59.520
Hey, don't make that face.

00:11:59.600 --> 00:12:01.360
That's not the Som I know.

00:12:04.200 --> 00:12:06.840
Smile. Come on.

00:12:07.360 --> 00:12:08.680
Arnon.

00:12:08.760 --> 00:12:10.640
There, that's better.

00:12:10.720 --> 00:12:12.800
Hey, I'm not a kid anymore.

00:12:12.880 --> 00:12:16.120
Som, come have lunch with me.

00:12:16.200 --> 00:12:20.640
I feel like it's been chaos all day,
the office,

00:12:20.720 --> 00:12:25.040
Ms. Mysterious, Jirasin,
and now the anklet.

00:12:25.120 --> 00:12:29.200
But Arnon, there's way more
important things than that.

00:12:29.840 --> 00:12:31.120
Like what?

00:12:31.720 --> 00:12:34.840
Treat me to lunch, okay?

00:12:39.520 --> 00:12:40.640
Please.

00:12:44.400 --> 00:12:47.560
Inviting you to eat
doesn't mean I'm paying.

00:12:49.360 --> 00:12:51.920
Fine, I'll treat you then.

00:12:52.000 --> 00:12:54.960
But can I borrow the money first?

00:12:57.440 --> 00:12:59.800
-Here, let me help.
-No, it's okay. I'll do it.

00:13:01.080 --> 00:13:02.080
Okay.

00:13:02.160 --> 00:13:04.760
Did you check
the location of those two yet?

00:13:04.840 --> 00:13:05.960
Mr. Pong and Mrs. Soi?

00:13:06.040 --> 00:13:08.480
Just like Mr. Arnon said,

00:13:08.560 --> 00:13:11.800
that whole neighborhood's been replaced
by condominiums.

00:13:11.880 --> 00:13:14.560
Even if we go there,
it'll be hard to get information.

00:13:15.160 --> 00:13:16.440
Grandma Aom said

00:13:17.000 --> 00:13:19.840
those two were
Ms. Ampha's childhood friends.

00:13:20.800 --> 00:13:23.840
When she became my father's wife,

00:13:25.680 --> 00:13:29.440
they moved in with her, right?

00:13:30.160 --> 00:13:31.200
Yes.

00:13:31.280 --> 00:13:34.320
So that would've been

00:13:35.160 --> 00:13:38.640
over 20 years ago?

00:13:38.720 --> 00:13:40.080
Well.

00:13:40.160 --> 00:13:42.320
If you were three at the time,

00:13:43.600 --> 00:13:45.520
then yes, over 20 years ago.

00:13:45.600 --> 00:13:48.480
The houses in that area are old.

00:13:49.720 --> 00:13:52.760
Most of the domestic workers
work there for a long time.

00:13:54.760 --> 00:13:55.920
You get

00:13:56.560 --> 00:13:57.640
what I mean, right?

00:13:59.320 --> 00:14:00.160
No.

00:14:00.240 --> 00:14:02.160
The employees from neighboring houses.

00:14:02.800 --> 00:14:05.600
There has to be someone
who remembers those two.

00:14:05.680 --> 00:14:07.280
Oh.

00:14:07.360 --> 00:14:10.800
You mean
we investigate through the neighbors?

00:14:10.880 --> 00:14:11.720
Exactly.

00:14:12.720 --> 00:14:16.400
But there are dozens
of houses around there.

00:14:16.480 --> 00:14:18.720
I'm not taking you on a grand tour.

00:14:18.800 --> 00:14:20.400
Just one house is enough.

00:14:20.480 --> 00:14:21.960
Whose house?

00:14:22.040 --> 00:14:23.160
Ameena's.

00:14:25.200 --> 00:14:26.920
I forgot to tell you.

00:14:27.800 --> 00:14:30.240
Ameena and I are distant relatives.

00:14:31.040 --> 00:14:34.400
Our families have known each other
since my grandmother's generation.

00:14:35.440 --> 00:14:37.800
We only drifted apart in my generation.

00:14:37.880 --> 00:14:39.120
It's three alleys down.

00:14:42.040 --> 00:14:44.960
No. I'm not going to Ameena's house.

00:14:48.800 --> 00:14:52.200
Didn't you say
you'd do anything to help Ms. Mysterious?

00:14:54.040 --> 00:14:56.760
Everything has exceptions.

00:14:57.360 --> 00:14:58.360
Up to you.

00:14:59.240 --> 00:15:00.560
Well.

00:15:01.240 --> 00:15:03.360
Ms. Ampha, you heard that, right?

00:15:03.440 --> 00:15:05.320
That's as far as she's willing to help.

00:15:05.400 --> 00:15:07.760
Mr. Warat, don't say that.

00:15:07.840 --> 00:15:09.880
I apologize on Kluay's behalf.

00:15:10.400 --> 00:15:11.560
I've done my best.

00:15:11.640 --> 00:15:14.280
Mr. Warat, please don't say that.

00:15:14.360 --> 00:15:15.320
‎No.

00:15:15.840 --> 00:15:17.800
I just don't want to go.

00:15:21.520 --> 00:15:23.880
Sorry, I think
I've come to the wrong room.

00:15:23.960 --> 00:15:25.880
No, this is the right room.

00:15:25.960 --> 00:15:28.960
If you're here for the company president,
it's here.

00:15:29.040 --> 00:15:32.800
But if want to go to the Legal Department
to investigate corruption,

00:15:33.840 --> 00:15:36.400
go straight and turn left.

00:15:36.480 --> 00:15:38.760
Staff are on standby.

00:15:42.320 --> 00:15:44.200
It seems

00:15:44.280 --> 00:15:47.400
someone brought
something bad to the house.

00:15:48.000 --> 00:15:51.320
Warat was the one who pointed it out.

00:15:51.400 --> 00:15:54.440
As for me, I didn't see

00:15:54.520 --> 00:15:56.520
anything unusual.

00:15:57.160 --> 00:15:58.600
But still,

00:15:58.680 --> 00:16:02.280
Feng Shui master, please help check,
just for my peace of mind.

00:16:06.920 --> 00:16:07.960
Food-related?

00:16:08.040 --> 00:16:11.240
Close. It was fruit.

00:16:11.880 --> 00:16:13.240
One moment.

00:16:19.040 --> 00:16:22.920
I should still have
the Vanich residence location.

00:16:24.480 --> 00:16:26.160
Here it is.

00:16:32.360 --> 00:16:37.560
I didn't see any feedback from you
about Phuket.

00:16:37.640 --> 00:16:39.400
So I'm not sure

00:16:39.480 --> 00:16:41.680
if you've received the latest file.

00:16:41.760 --> 00:16:42.600
Here.

00:16:47.240 --> 00:16:48.280
Let's do one thing at a time.

00:16:48.360 --> 00:16:50.680
-Yes.
-I heard

00:16:51.440 --> 00:16:53.360
you sent something to my house again?

00:16:53.440 --> 00:16:56.640
Yes. I didn't know you would be here.

00:16:56.720 --> 00:16:58.800
Otherwise, I would've brought it here.

00:16:59.880 --> 00:17:01.680
I'll wait outside.

00:17:01.760 --> 00:17:02.680
No need.

00:17:04.560 --> 00:17:08.960
If you leave, who will explain to him
what filthy thing…

00:17:11.040 --> 00:17:12.920
was attached to what he sent?

00:17:13.960 --> 00:17:17.400
Filthy? What was attached, Kluay?

00:17:17.480 --> 00:17:20.000
Where did you get that fruit, Sin?

00:17:20.079 --> 00:17:22.160
I bought it myself. What's wrong?

00:17:23.839 --> 00:17:26.319
There was a wandering spirit
attached to it.

00:17:28.520 --> 00:17:30.160
A wandering spirit?

00:17:30.800 --> 00:17:31.960
How is that even possible?

00:17:32.040 --> 00:17:37.200
It had previously been used
as an offering to spirits.

00:17:37.280 --> 00:17:39.720
Enough. No need to explain to him.

00:17:39.800 --> 00:17:44.000
From now on, nothing from you
will ever enter my house again.

00:17:44.080 --> 00:17:46.600
Mr. Warat, I understand.

00:17:46.680 --> 00:17:47.960
If I were you,

00:17:49.920 --> 00:17:52.400
and lost my position
as the chairwoman's favorite…

00:17:53.200 --> 00:17:55.040
But I wouldn't

00:17:55.120 --> 00:17:57.720
team up with someone
who sees ghosts and spins fairy tales.

00:17:57.800 --> 00:17:58.960
It's ridiculous.

00:17:59.040 --> 00:18:01.920
Jirasin, apologize to Kluay right now.

00:18:02.000 --> 00:18:04.080
What she said is true.

00:18:04.720 --> 00:18:07.640
So she's proven to you

00:18:07.720 --> 00:18:10.480
that she's not lying?

00:18:14.120 --> 00:18:15.120
Mr. Warat.

00:18:15.200 --> 00:18:16.360
Where's the ghost?

00:18:17.120 --> 00:18:18.200
Where's the spirit?

00:18:18.280 --> 00:18:19.360
Where's the psychic power?

00:18:19.960 --> 00:18:21.520
Get out.

00:18:21.600 --> 00:18:22.840
Fine.

00:18:23.400 --> 00:18:24.960
I'm not angry.

00:18:25.760 --> 00:18:29.080
But one day, you'll thank me.

00:18:30.200 --> 00:18:31.360
Sin.

00:18:35.440 --> 00:18:36.480
Don't go to the construction site today.

00:18:37.800 --> 00:18:39.520
Did you investigate my schedule

00:18:39.600 --> 00:18:40.920
and see that I'm going to the site today?

00:18:43.400 --> 00:18:45.440
Don't go there.

00:18:53.760 --> 00:18:54.720
Kluay.

00:18:56.920 --> 00:18:57.920
What happened?

00:18:59.440 --> 00:19:00.640
What did you see?

00:19:01.960 --> 00:19:03.040
Sin

00:19:04.040 --> 00:19:06.160
is about to face a serious accident.

00:19:07.600 --> 00:19:08.920
It could be fatal.

00:19:13.840 --> 00:19:15.400
How is it?

00:19:20.760 --> 00:19:24.000
I analyzed the energy from the date, time,

00:19:24.080 --> 00:19:26.360
and when the fruit entered the house.

00:19:32.440 --> 00:19:33.360
That fruit…

00:19:34.120 --> 00:19:37.200
There was something in it like Warat said?

00:19:45.480 --> 00:19:46.320
No.

00:19:52.000 --> 00:19:55.040
Hearing that relieves me, Master.

00:19:55.640 --> 00:19:59.040
I only predicted based
on initial energy readings.

00:19:59.640 --> 00:20:02.760
But I still need to inspect
the Vanich house again

00:20:02.840 --> 00:20:04.240
to be 100% sure.

00:20:05.000 --> 00:20:06.160
Very well.

00:20:06.920 --> 00:20:08.800
-Supol.
-Yes, ma'am.

00:20:09.400 --> 00:20:13.640
Once the master arrives, explain to him

00:20:13.720 --> 00:20:15.040
what happened.

00:20:15.120 --> 00:20:18.920
With the utmost respect, I'll handle it.

00:20:19.000 --> 00:20:19.880
Please.

00:20:20.800 --> 00:20:22.080
Then I'll excuse myself now.

00:20:22.680 --> 00:20:24.160
-Goodbye.
-Goodbye.

00:20:28.520 --> 00:20:29.600
All set.

00:20:33.400 --> 00:20:35.720
The chairwoman
trusts Master Pong completely.

00:20:45.120 --> 00:20:46.360
-Let's go.
-I remember him.

00:20:46.920 --> 00:20:49.200
He's a fortune teller. His name is…

00:20:49.280 --> 00:20:50.800
Master Pong.

00:20:51.320 --> 00:20:53.480
He's a major debtor to Boss Peng.

00:20:53.560 --> 00:20:56.800
He fled to LA for years,
came back because his mother died.

00:20:57.440 --> 00:20:58.720
He's very famous.

00:20:58.800 --> 00:21:00.400
He regularly reads fortunes for our mall.

00:21:02.920 --> 00:21:04.480
The chairwoman highly respects him.

00:21:05.080 --> 00:21:06.480
He's finished.

00:21:06.560 --> 00:21:08.720
He owes Boss Peng hundreds of millions.

00:21:08.800 --> 00:21:10.240
Maybe even billions.

00:21:10.320 --> 00:21:12.000
That's why he's hiding like this.

00:21:12.920 --> 00:21:14.280
I want to talk to him.

00:21:15.480 --> 00:21:16.520
Have him come speak with me.

00:21:18.680 --> 00:21:20.720
It's like heaven sent Master Pong to us.

00:21:21.840 --> 00:21:23.120
We would've been finished

00:21:23.200 --> 00:21:26.520
if the chairwoman had believed
your fruit was an offering to spirits.

00:21:27.120 --> 00:21:29.680
That would count as cursing her.

00:21:30.480 --> 00:21:32.840
It's over. Don't bring it up again.

00:21:32.920 --> 00:21:35.480
Are you heading to the construction site?

00:21:35.560 --> 00:21:36.520
Yes.

00:21:37.120 --> 00:21:41.000
The technical team said there's an issue
with the cement and steel specs.

00:21:41.880 --> 00:21:43.160
That's unfortunate.

00:21:43.240 --> 00:21:46.240
Interior work is supposed to be easy,
yet it's the one with problems.

00:21:46.760 --> 00:21:47.880
That's just how it is.

00:21:54.040 --> 00:21:55.760
Didn't you want to talk to me about this?

00:21:57.080 --> 00:21:58.080
Mr. Warat.

00:21:59.240 --> 00:22:01.480
I'm starting to lose my patience with you.

00:22:01.560 --> 00:22:04.920
If you've lost your patience,
then the project in the file

00:22:05.000 --> 00:22:06.520
is canceled.

00:22:07.840 --> 00:22:08.800
Excuse me.

00:22:09.520 --> 00:22:11.680
Don't you think
that's a bit rash, Mr. Warat?

00:22:12.600 --> 00:22:16.280
Mr. Jirasin and I
worked very hard on this project.

00:22:16.360 --> 00:22:19.040
Saying something like that
is discouraging. It's not okay.

00:22:19.760 --> 00:22:22.000
I want to talk to you about this too.

00:22:22.880 --> 00:22:25.800
Why does a Procurement executive like you

00:22:26.480 --> 00:22:28.680
have your name listed as a shareholder

00:22:28.760 --> 00:22:32.200
in new projects, especially
the ones Mr. Jirasin is handling?

00:22:33.160 --> 00:22:36.440
If you're looking to pick a fight,
let's do it another day.

00:22:36.520 --> 00:22:38.640
I have work to do. Let's go.

00:22:57.680 --> 00:22:59.560
Sin, a beam collapsed at the site.

00:22:59.640 --> 00:23:00.440
Please hurry.

00:23:01.080 --> 00:23:02.200
Is anyone hurt?

00:23:02.280 --> 00:23:03.360
Have you called an ambulance?

00:23:03.440 --> 00:23:06.080
Rescue and ambulance units
are already on standby.

00:23:07.600 --> 00:23:08.760
How did they get there so fast?

00:23:09.280 --> 00:23:10.320
Who called them?

00:23:11.680 --> 00:23:13.040
Don't go to the construction site.

00:23:13.560 --> 00:23:15.520
Don't go there.

00:23:27.520 --> 00:23:30.680
So we managed to block access
to the site just in time, right?

00:23:31.440 --> 00:23:34.640
Okay, good. I'm heading down to check.

00:23:34.720 --> 00:23:36.800
-How is it?
-Kluay.

00:23:37.840 --> 00:23:39.680
Yes, it's me.

00:23:40.200 --> 00:23:43.880
Don't tell me you're so worried about
Jirasin that you came here to wait for me.

00:23:44.920 --> 00:23:48.520
Yes, I'm worried. Very worried.

00:23:52.640 --> 00:23:55.880
No matter who it is, I would worry

00:23:55.960 --> 00:23:59.160
if I were about to see
them die in front of me.

00:23:59.240 --> 00:24:02.600
By the way,
Sin didn't leave his room, right?

00:24:07.600 --> 00:24:09.040
That's a relief.

00:24:09.840 --> 00:24:12.120
No one at the site was hurt. I just…

00:24:13.840 --> 00:24:15.080
Mr. Warat.

00:24:15.160 --> 00:24:16.800
Wait.

00:24:32.960 --> 00:24:35.560
You got here fast. No traffic?

00:24:35.640 --> 00:24:38.360
Or were you in such a rush
you took a motorcycle taxi?

00:24:41.240 --> 00:24:42.600
Don't talk so much.

00:24:43.240 --> 00:24:44.680
How much do you want?

00:24:44.760 --> 00:24:46.920
Just say it. I'm ready to transfer.

00:24:47.600 --> 00:24:50.960
You think I'd waste my precious time

00:24:51.040 --> 00:24:52.720
digging up your filth

00:24:52.800 --> 00:24:54.960
for your dirty scraps of money?

00:24:56.000 --> 00:24:57.720
What else would you want if not money?

00:24:58.600 --> 00:24:59.840
Do you say things like that,

00:24:59.920 --> 00:25:01.800
because you're old and brainless,

00:25:01.880 --> 00:25:04.880
-or is it dementia?
-Som.

00:25:04.960 --> 00:25:08.760
Go tell Jirasin
that Kluay didn't kill his sister.

00:25:11.240 --> 00:25:12.880
Why should I?

00:25:12.960 --> 00:25:15.520
You still wonder why? It's because of you

00:25:15.600 --> 00:25:17.800
that Jirasin keeps targeting Kluay.

00:25:17.880 --> 00:25:21.480
You and Det saw with your own eyes
that Lakkana fell down the stairs herself,

00:25:21.560 --> 00:25:25.520
but you kept quiet and let Jirasin
believe Kluay was a murderer.

00:25:26.520 --> 00:25:27.600
Hey.

00:25:28.280 --> 00:25:30.040
If Kluay is really innocent,

00:25:30.760 --> 00:25:31.840
what is she afraid of?

00:25:40.800 --> 00:25:42.080
Say it.

00:25:42.160 --> 00:25:44.480
We were wrong.

00:25:45.160 --> 00:25:47.640
A woman named Ameena hired us.

00:25:47.720 --> 00:25:49.320
What did she hire you to do?

00:25:49.400 --> 00:25:51.320
She hired me to pretend to be

00:25:51.400 --> 00:25:54.320
-the wife and slap the mistress, Kluay.
-Enough. Stop.

00:25:54.400 --> 00:25:56.240
Are you sure
this is the name of the hirer?

00:25:56.920 --> 00:25:58.680
It's Ameena. One hundred percent.

00:26:00.480 --> 00:26:02.760
Fine. I give up.

00:26:03.360 --> 00:26:04.800
That's it.

00:26:05.480 --> 00:26:06.960
I'll…

00:26:07.760 --> 00:26:09.600
I'll have

00:26:10.120 --> 00:26:12.440
Det talk to Sin.

00:26:13.200 --> 00:26:18.160
No. If Det talking worked,
this would've been over long ago.

00:26:18.240 --> 00:26:20.320
Jirasin doesn't believe him.

00:26:20.400 --> 00:26:23.480
He thinks Det
would side with Kluay anyway.

00:26:24.920 --> 00:26:27.920
Then go tell Kluay
to stop throwing herself at Det.

00:26:28.000 --> 00:26:29.240
Oh?

00:26:29.920 --> 00:26:31.240
What did you just say?

00:26:33.120 --> 00:26:37.080
Fine, fine, I surrender. I'll…

00:26:37.160 --> 00:26:38.640
I'll talk to him myself.

00:26:38.720 --> 00:26:40.360
What are you going to say?

00:26:40.440 --> 00:26:42.760
I'll say that…

00:26:42.840 --> 00:26:45.120
Well…

00:26:45.200 --> 00:26:48.800
-Is it so hard to say?
-I'm not good at talking.

00:26:48.880 --> 00:26:50.360
I'm thinking about what to say.

00:26:50.440 --> 00:26:52.280
I'll talk to him, but

00:26:52.360 --> 00:26:55.240
whether Sin

00:26:55.320 --> 00:26:57.480
believes it or not is not my fault.

00:26:57.560 --> 00:26:59.960
I'll do what I have to do.

00:27:00.040 --> 00:27:02.280
Yes, but

00:27:02.360 --> 00:27:05.880
your clip and all your filthy secrets,

00:27:05.960 --> 00:27:07.880
I'm posting it on social media today.

00:27:07.960 --> 00:27:09.400
Oh, no.

00:27:09.480 --> 00:27:11.640
I won't do that. I'll post it right now.

00:27:11.720 --> 00:27:13.040
Hey. Fine, fine. I'll talk.

00:27:13.120 --> 00:27:15.160
I'll say it myself. I'll say it myself.

00:27:15.240 --> 00:27:16.360
I'll say it.

00:27:17.280 --> 00:27:19.640
Good. And don't be sneaky

00:27:19.720 --> 00:27:22.680
because I'm not Kluay. Remember that.

00:27:34.360 --> 00:27:35.920
Mr. Warat, wait for me.

00:27:36.000 --> 00:27:37.680
Okay, I know you're angry.

00:27:37.760 --> 00:27:40.280
Fine. From now on,
I won't care about Sin anymore.

00:27:40.360 --> 00:27:43.080
What?
You think I'm jealous of that bastard?

00:27:43.160 --> 00:27:44.560
No, no.

00:27:44.640 --> 00:27:47.480
That's not what I meant. I mean…

00:27:47.560 --> 00:27:51.200
I'm angry because the investigation
into Mr. Pong and Mrs. Soi

00:27:51.280 --> 00:27:52.800
hasn't made any progress at all.

00:27:52.880 --> 00:27:53.800
But you…

00:27:53.880 --> 00:27:55.520
We haven't gotten anything done

00:27:55.600 --> 00:27:57.080
because you keep thinking about that guy.

00:27:57.160 --> 00:27:59.520
But you were the one
who decided on your own

00:27:59.600 --> 00:28:01.000
not to let Sin go to the site.

00:28:01.080 --> 00:28:03.600
We were talking normally,
then I turned around

00:28:03.680 --> 00:28:05.000
and you were already in Sin's office.

00:28:05.080 --> 00:28:08.280
If I'd let you go talk to him,
would he have listened to you?

00:28:08.360 --> 00:28:09.880
At that moment, it had to be me.

00:28:11.000 --> 00:28:12.560
You did the right thing.

00:28:12.640 --> 00:28:15.760
You wouldn't want
to see Sin hurt or die either.

00:28:15.840 --> 00:28:16.680
You did great.

00:28:18.240 --> 00:28:20.160
Don't make this dramatic. It's nauseating.

00:28:20.240 --> 00:28:21.560
Mr. Warat.

00:28:23.840 --> 00:28:24.880
Be careful about Grandma.

00:28:24.960 --> 00:28:26.840
Don't forget you can't walk on your own.

00:28:26.920 --> 00:28:28.720
I'll tell Grandma I've recovered.

00:28:28.800 --> 00:28:29.800
No.

00:28:29.880 --> 00:28:31.960
You know I still have to stay here.

00:28:32.040 --> 00:28:34.200
I still have to help Ms. Ampha.

00:28:34.280 --> 00:28:36.880
Go spend your time
helping that bastard of yours.

00:28:37.560 --> 00:28:40.440
"That bastard"? You're being unreasonable.

00:28:42.040 --> 00:28:45.080
Warat, you've taken off your cast?

00:28:45.680 --> 00:28:46.600
Yes.

00:28:47.240 --> 00:28:49.440
But he still can't walk properly.

00:28:51.440 --> 00:28:54.600
Today I invited a Feng Shui master
to check the house

00:28:54.680 --> 00:28:56.880
about the spirits you mentioned.

00:28:56.960 --> 00:28:58.080
Did he find anything?

00:28:58.680 --> 00:28:59.760
No.

00:29:01.520 --> 00:29:03.280
And there never was anything.

00:29:05.120 --> 00:29:06.160
What do you mean?

00:29:06.760 --> 00:29:09.320
Please allow me to clarify.

00:29:09.400 --> 00:29:11.280
The Feng Shui master
inspected the house thoroughly

00:29:11.360 --> 00:29:12.960
and said everything was normal.

00:29:13.040 --> 00:29:14.680
There was nothing unusual.

00:29:14.760 --> 00:29:18.120
And the fruit that you claimed
had something bad attached to it,

00:29:18.200 --> 00:29:21.680
he examined it carefully
and repeatedly confirmed

00:29:21.760 --> 00:29:23.240
that it was not as you said.

00:29:23.320 --> 00:29:24.560
That's not true.

00:29:24.640 --> 00:29:27.040
That's impossible. Kluay saw it herself.

00:29:27.680 --> 00:29:30.520
She saw it. And did you?

00:29:33.280 --> 00:29:34.560
Uh…

00:29:34.640 --> 00:29:37.640
It's good that there's nothing wrong.

00:29:37.720 --> 00:29:39.640
I'm happy for you.

00:29:39.720 --> 00:29:40.920
Warat,

00:29:41.000 --> 00:29:43.200
I think we should go upstairs and rest.

00:29:43.280 --> 00:29:44.320
Wait.

00:29:44.400 --> 00:29:46.160
Let me ask you this.

00:29:46.800 --> 00:29:49.320
Why did you make up that ghost story?

00:29:49.920 --> 00:29:52.840
Grandma, Kluay didn't make it up.

00:30:00.840 --> 00:30:04.680
It's fine. I can handle it. You can go.

00:30:06.200 --> 00:30:07.880
What's wrong with you?

00:30:07.960 --> 00:30:09.720
You're still making things up?

00:30:10.400 --> 00:30:13.080
Warat, I won't tolerate this anymore.

00:30:13.160 --> 00:30:15.520
If Kluay still keeps rambling like this…

00:30:21.360 --> 00:30:22.320
What's this?

00:30:22.400 --> 00:30:24.880
Supol, didn't you change
the light bulbs for me?

00:30:24.960 --> 00:30:28.440
With the utmost respect, ma'am,
I've ordered all the bulbs replaced.

00:30:28.520 --> 00:30:31.760
Then that means
the bulbs this time are poor quality.

00:30:33.280 --> 00:30:34.160
Ma'am.

00:30:34.240 --> 00:30:37.240
I don't think this has anything
to do with the quality of the bulbs.

00:30:38.800 --> 00:30:40.560
Please don't do this, Ms. Ampha.

00:30:43.800 --> 00:30:44.920
Ampha?

00:30:51.240 --> 00:30:52.920
If Mr. Warat
hadn't come in at that moment,

00:30:53.000 --> 00:30:56.560
I can't imagine
how it would've turned out.

00:30:56.640 --> 00:30:59.240
I might've been crushed by the beam too,

00:30:59.320 --> 00:31:01.600
because I was planning
to follow you to the site.

00:31:02.600 --> 00:31:04.360
Warat didn't intend to come talk to me.

00:31:05.320 --> 00:31:06.440
What do you mean?

00:31:07.480 --> 00:31:08.840
He knew something would happen.

00:31:10.480 --> 00:31:13.720
Like some kind of premonition?

00:31:15.720 --> 00:31:18.840
Why do I feel like you've been
obsessed with mysterious things lately?

00:31:19.440 --> 00:31:23.440
First ghosts at the Vanich house,
and now Mr. Warat having a premonition?

00:31:25.000 --> 00:31:26.680
Exactly. Nonsense.

00:31:26.760 --> 00:31:29.120
Someone like Warat
wouldn't care about my life.

00:31:37.240 --> 00:31:40.280
Why did Ms. Ameena ask to meet you?

00:31:42.040 --> 00:31:43.640
I'd like to know too.

00:31:43.720 --> 00:31:46.080
Must be important,
otherwise, she wouldn't call so suddenly.

00:31:52.360 --> 00:31:54.360
I thought you would come alone.

00:31:56.280 --> 00:31:59.080
It's alright. This is Mr. Chatchai.

00:32:08.080 --> 00:32:11.920
But what I want to talk about

00:32:12.800 --> 00:32:17.080
is about Lakkana, your sister, and Kluay.

00:32:23.280 --> 00:32:24.560
Please go ahead.

00:32:24.640 --> 00:32:26.640
Don't worry about me listening in.

00:32:26.720 --> 00:32:29.640
I already know about this.

00:32:31.160 --> 00:32:32.160
Well.

00:32:33.440 --> 00:32:35.440
I'm here to tell you…

00:32:38.320 --> 00:32:42.600
that Kluay didn't kill Lakkana.

00:32:58.640 --> 00:33:00.760
Anong. Anong.

00:33:01.520 --> 00:33:03.600
Anong. It's me, Kaew.

00:33:12.640 --> 00:33:14.120
You haven't aged at all.

00:33:15.480 --> 00:33:18.000
Why are you here? I told you

00:33:18.600 --> 00:33:20.080
we don't need to see each other again.

00:33:20.680 --> 00:33:23.000
I know. I don't want to see you either.

00:33:24.160 --> 00:33:27.080
But I came to warn you
someone is digging into Pong and Soi.

00:33:28.240 --> 00:33:29.960
Do you know who they are?

00:33:31.440 --> 00:33:33.160
Didn't you say

00:33:33.720 --> 00:33:36.280
you already took care of them?

00:33:37.560 --> 00:33:39.760
And the owner of that orphanage

00:33:40.640 --> 00:33:42.240
is already dead.

00:33:47.680 --> 00:33:49.240
Or did you just scam money from me?

00:33:49.320 --> 00:33:53.000
Hey, my men ran him over.
He died right there.

00:33:53.080 --> 00:33:54.680
Don't talk nonsense like that.

00:33:56.600 --> 00:33:59.320
Then who's digging into Pong and Soi?

00:33:59.920 --> 00:34:00.880
I don't know.

00:34:00.960 --> 00:34:04.040
I just came to warn you. That's all.

00:34:04.640 --> 00:34:08.040
Most importantly, if anything happens,
don't drag me into it.

00:34:08.120 --> 00:34:09.760
My wife just gave birth.

00:34:09.840 --> 00:34:11.880
I don't want anything
to do with this anymore.

00:34:13.120 --> 00:34:14.719
I'm telling you nicely.

00:34:16.400 --> 00:34:17.600
Are you threatening me?

00:34:17.679 --> 00:34:20.000
If I were threatening you,
I wouldn't come like this.

00:34:20.080 --> 00:34:21.199
You know me.

00:34:29.920 --> 00:34:31.600
Or is it that girl?

00:34:34.080 --> 00:34:37.239
I told you to finish her off.

00:34:37.320 --> 00:34:38.960
And you didn't.

00:34:39.040 --> 00:34:41.040
Things had quieted down.

00:34:41.120 --> 00:34:42.480
You're the stingy one.

00:34:42.560 --> 00:34:44.040
You wouldn't pay extra.

00:34:44.120 --> 00:34:46.320
Who works for free?

00:34:47.040 --> 00:34:49.440
Anong, where are you?

00:34:49.520 --> 00:34:50.760
Go inside.

00:34:51.760 --> 00:34:52.800
And remember.

00:34:53.920 --> 00:34:55.239
Don't let this trace back to me.

00:35:00.320 --> 00:35:02.400
Do you hear me? I'm calling you, Anong.

00:35:03.760 --> 00:35:06.160
Anong. Anong!

00:35:09.280 --> 00:35:10.280
Yes?

00:35:18.200 --> 00:35:19.480
Madam is praying.

00:35:19.560 --> 00:35:21.360
I think the two of you should rest.

00:35:21.440 --> 00:35:22.560
No need to wait.

00:35:23.360 --> 00:35:26.360
Then I'll take Warat up first
and come back to wait for Grandma.

00:35:26.440 --> 00:35:30.200
If you want to talk about the past,
I don't think she wants to.

00:35:30.960 --> 00:35:33.920
Grandma has already seen
that Kluay really had a premonition,

00:35:35.240 --> 00:35:36.640
that she sees things.

00:35:36.720 --> 00:35:37.920
Why avoid it?

00:35:38.000 --> 00:35:39.280
Come on. I'll talk to Grandma myself.

00:35:39.360 --> 00:35:42.480
With the utmost respect,
I'm begging you, Mr. Warat.

00:35:48.560 --> 00:35:50.160
Please listen to Mr. Supol.

00:35:50.240 --> 00:35:52.280
Let's wait in the room.

00:36:01.920 --> 00:36:03.600
Turns out he's walking just fine.

00:36:04.200 --> 00:36:05.120
He seems healthy.

00:36:06.640 --> 00:36:07.480
Yes.

00:36:22.960 --> 00:36:24.280
Thank you.

00:36:25.040 --> 00:36:27.200
Oh. Why are there only two?

00:36:28.320 --> 00:36:30.440
Grandma left for the temple
early this morning.

00:36:31.280 --> 00:36:35.160
She told the housekeeper
she might go to the office afterward.

00:36:38.040 --> 00:36:39.680
She's deliberately avoiding me

00:36:41.240 --> 00:36:43.520
because she knows
I'll ask about Ms. Ampha.

00:36:44.480 --> 00:36:45.920
It's alright.

00:36:46.000 --> 00:36:49.080
She's never told us about the past anyway.

00:36:49.160 --> 00:36:51.400
If she suddenly did today,
that would be strange.

00:36:52.720 --> 00:36:54.680
Here. Eat.

00:36:56.040 --> 00:36:57.840
No. I'm not hungry.

00:36:59.280 --> 00:37:02.520
And your foot…

00:37:02.600 --> 00:37:04.480
I think it's time to stop acting.

00:37:04.560 --> 00:37:06.960
Since Grandma doesn't care how I feel.

00:37:08.640 --> 00:37:10.560
Then why argue with her?

00:37:10.640 --> 00:37:13.480
The more you push,
the harder you make things for me.

00:37:13.560 --> 00:37:16.600
Let's go. We have to hurry.

00:37:16.680 --> 00:37:19.360
Wait. I haven't finished eating.

00:37:20.160 --> 00:37:21.040
Hurry up.

00:37:24.840 --> 00:37:26.640
Hey. Hey.

00:37:37.200 --> 00:37:39.080
Hello, it's Baan Saeng Wan Mai.

00:37:40.160 --> 00:37:41.520
Are you contacting
the registry department?

00:37:41.600 --> 00:37:43.960
You can ask me.

00:37:44.040 --> 00:37:47.360
If you need more details,
please wait for an officer.

00:37:47.440 --> 00:37:48.720
Is 9 a.m. convenient?

00:37:48.800 --> 00:37:50.520
Your private taxi has arrived.

00:37:52.920 --> 00:37:55.720
I'd like to ask about a child there.

00:37:55.800 --> 00:37:58.920
I made a donation a long time ago.

00:37:59.000 --> 00:38:01.360
I just want to know

00:38:01.440 --> 00:38:04.040
how she's doing now,

00:38:04.120 --> 00:38:06.960
what grade she is in?

00:38:07.040 --> 00:38:10.160
Sure. Thank you so much
for caring about the children.

00:38:10.240 --> 00:38:12.680
An officer will call you back.

00:38:12.760 --> 00:38:15.880
May I ask what the child's name is?

00:38:18.440 --> 00:38:19.960
You don't remember?

00:38:21.280 --> 00:38:22.480
Then I'm afraid not.

00:38:22.560 --> 00:38:24.960
We cannot provide the children's names.

00:38:25.040 --> 00:38:26.360
I'm sorry.

00:38:27.000 --> 00:38:28.040
Really?

00:38:29.000 --> 00:38:32.000
What if the name is…

00:38:32.680 --> 00:38:33.720
What's the name again?

00:38:33.800 --> 00:38:35.040
It's…

00:38:35.680 --> 00:38:36.880
Who are you talking to, Anong?

00:38:44.720 --> 00:38:48.200
Actually, the two of us
are getting married.

00:38:48.280 --> 00:38:49.520
NEXT EPISODE

00:38:49.600 --> 00:38:52.280
I thought Ameena
had already cleared things up with you.

00:38:52.360 --> 00:38:54.240
Why are you still bothering my sister?

00:38:55.760 --> 00:38:58.120
Whatever dreams you have
about making him great,

00:38:58.200 --> 00:38:59.880
I'll ruin them completely.

00:38:59.960 --> 00:39:01.000
Sin!

00:39:01.080 --> 00:39:04.480
Is it possible that to Uncle Sarut,

00:39:04.560 --> 00:39:07.000
I'm not just the son of his ex-lover?

00:39:07.600 --> 00:39:09.960
Boonsita, no matter what you see,

00:39:10.040 --> 00:39:12.360
stop everything.

00:39:12.440 --> 00:39:15.680
Don't let Warat see
or know anything ever again.

00:41:38.520 --> 00:41:42.240
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon